going on.

28:57.000 --> 29:01.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
CATHERINE SPARKS: What's
been the most painful
about the proliferation
of fake news in the

29:02.600 --> 29:06.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
media is to watch my students
start to distrust everything.

29:06.500 --> 29:11.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: That's
exactly why state Senator Marko
Liias says media literacy is

29:11.466 --> 29:13.966 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
so important.

29:13.966 --> 29:16.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARKO LIIAS: At its
bedrock, when our founding
fathers created this
country, the reason why

29:16.833 --> 29:21.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they were so committed to public
education was to make sure that
we had an educated citizenry.

29:23.800 --> 29:27.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CATHERINE SPARKS: Anything that
starts with "share if you're
outraged," that's a bad sign.

29:28.866 --> 29:31.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And outrage is just the
lifeblood of fake news.

29:31.566 --> 29:36.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: For the "PBS
NewsHour" and Education Week,
I'm Kavitha Cardoza in Seattle,

29:39.133 --> 29:41.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Washington.

29:41.933 --> 29:46.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Aid
organizations, especially
those working in conflict
zones like Yemen,

29:52.200 --> 29:55.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
say it's crucial that they
remain politically neutral.

29:55.766 --> 29:59.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They say it's the only way
they can safely do their jobs.

29:59.133 --> 30:04.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But a recent investigation by
The New York Times reveals how
one company may have endangered

30:05.266 --> 30:07.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that neutrality for many
humanitarian groups.

30:07.966 --> 30:10.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
William Brangham has that story.

30:10.100 --> 30:13.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: UNICEF and
the Red Cross are two of the
humanitarian groups working

30:13.333 --> 30:18.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Yemen, where a brutal civil
war has killed or injured
at least 12,000 people.

30:20.300 --> 30:23.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Times today revealed that
a logistics company known
as Transoceanic Development

30:23.133 --> 30:28.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
wasn't only helping those aid
groups get their supplies into
Yemen, but the company was also

30:28.000 --> 30:31.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
secretly helping U.S.
special forces do the same.

30:31.766 --> 30:36.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Times reports how this
dual relationship could drive
suspicion that the aid groups

30:36.333 --> 30:39.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
were somehow acting as agents
of the U.S. government.

30:39.433 --> 30:41.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I'm joined now by Eric Schmitt.

30:41.133 --> 30:43.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's one of The Times'
reporters who broke this story.

30:43.966 --> 30:46.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And by Daryl Grisgraber.

30:46.533 --> 30:49.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She's a senior advocate
at Refugees International,
which is an aid group
that operates in the

30:49.966 --> 30:52.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Middle East, Africa,
and Southeast Asia.

30:52.466 --> 30:54.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She previously worked for
Amnesty International.

30:54.933 --> 30:56.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Welcome to you both.

30:56.733 --> 30:58.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Eric Schmitt, I would
like to start with you.

30:58.466 --> 31:01.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Let's just go over some
of these details again.

31:01.100 --> 31:05.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So this logistics company,
Transoceanic Development,
is working to deliver
and help deliver aid

31:07.266 --> 31:12.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
supplies to Yemen for these
aid groups, while they're also
doing some work for U.S. special

31:14.166 --> 31:15.666 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
forces.

31:15.666 --> 31:16.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Can you explain those two
relationships a little bit?

31:16.866 --> 31:18.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
ERIC SCHMITT, The New
York Times: Right.

31:18.333 --> 31:21.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, Transoceanic is this giant
global logistics company.

31:21.333 --> 31:26.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And its job is really to ferry
materials and shipments all over
the world for various customers.

31:28.266 --> 31:31.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And a couple of its customers,
as you mentioned, are the
Red Cross and for UNICEF.

31:31.600 --> 31:36.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, in this case, they did
some warehousing, they did some
basic bringing materials and

31:38.633 --> 31:43.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
shipments of supplies into Yemen
that would then be delivered to
-- through other humanitarian

31:45.533 --> 31:50.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
organizations to the needy
in that strife-torn country.

31:50.266 --> 31:51.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So that's one of their jobs.

31:51.533 --> 31:53.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And they were very
open about this.

31:53.566 --> 31:57.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And when Mr. Darden was
kidnapped, his story became
quite public, because...

31:57.300 --> 32:02.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: This
is the main, the central
character in your story,
who was sort of organizing

32:03.166 --> 32:05.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
this organization in Yemen.

32:05.133 --> 32:08.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was kidnapped by some
rebels there, and then was
released after several years.

32:08.833 --> 32:10.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ERIC SCHMITT: That's right.

32:10.333 --> 32:12.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Scott Darden was the country
director for Transoceanic.

32:12.400 --> 32:17.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, he was responsible kind of
at the front end for getting
these shipments of aid into

32:18.733 --> 32:19.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yemen.

32:19.733 --> 32:21.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, that story is quite public.

32:21.700 --> 32:26.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What's new here is that it
turned out that Transoceanic
and Mr. Darden were also working

32:28.833 --> 32:32.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on secret contracts
involving shipping similar
types of materials into
Yemen for the military,

32:34.566 --> 32:38.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
specifically for the very
specialized special operations
forces, the commandos, who are

32:39.900 --> 32:41.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
operating in Yemen today.

32:41.833 --> 32:45.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: And just
for the record, there's no
evidence that the aid groups had

32:45.533 --> 32:50.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
any idea that the company they
were hiring to do work for
them was also doing this work

32:50.133 --> 32:51.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for the U.S. government.

32:51.266 --> 32:53.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ERIC SCHMITT: That's right.

32:53.400 --> 32:58.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Spokesmen for both UNICEF and
for the Red Cross said they
had no idea that Transoceanic

33:00.833 --> 33:05.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was carrying out these kind of
contracts with the military on
the logistics side of things.

33:05.733 --> 33:09.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And had they known, they may
have opted for another company.

33:09.033 --> 33:14.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I must say, there aren't a
lot of companies that get into
these kind of very dangerous

33:14.766 --> 33:16.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
war zone type of places.

33:16.833 --> 33:21.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So it's not unusual to find
a company like Transoceanic
dealing with multiple kinds of

33:22.133 --> 33:23.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
customers.

33:23.800 --> 33:25.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM:
So, Daryl Grisgraber,
what is your reaction?

33:25.433 --> 33:26.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You read this story.

33:26.566 --> 33:29.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What was your response?

33:29.166 --> 33:31.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DARYL GRISGRABER, Refugees
International: Initially,
we were all quite
dismayed as humanitarians,

33:31.300 --> 33:36.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
because there's meant to be a
very strict separation between
military assistance, political

33:37.266 --> 33:39.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
assistance, and
humanitarian assistance.

33:39.300 --> 33:42.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And there is quite a lively
debate that goes on right now
in the humanitarian world about

33:42.566 --> 33:47.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
keeping those separate
and when and how is it
possible to combine them.

33:47.300 --> 33:51.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the initial reaction
then is, because these got
combined, it's going to look bad

33:51.266 --> 33:53.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for humanitarians everywhere.

33:53.833 --> 33:58.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Humanitarians tend to
be a little bit under
suspicion anyway, just
because they're foreigners

34:00.500 --> 34:02.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
often in a country,
where we talk about
the U.N. or big INGOs.

34:02.566 --> 34:06.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And they operate very
significantly on trust,
building trust with
the people they serve,

34:07.966 --> 34:10.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as well as the governments
that allow them to operate.

34:10.433 --> 34:15.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And to know now that the
humanitarian principle
of neutrality in
particular has potentially

34:17.533 --> 34:21.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
been compromised or
even perceived to be
compromised is going to
affect all humanitarians.

34:21.000 --> 34:25.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: So, the
concern, just to spell it out
even more clearly, is that if

34:25.933 --> 34:30.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a government or groups operating
in a certain country somehow
thought that you were receiving

34:32.933 --> 34:36.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
shipments from a company that
was also working for a partisan
group in that nation as well,

34:37.900 --> 34:39.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that the humanitarian aid
workers might come under attack.

34:39.866 --> 34:41.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
DARYL GRISGRABER:
Oh, for sure, yes.

34:41.800 --> 34:44.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Organizations could be banned
from operating in a country.

34:44.066 --> 34:46.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The humanitarian individuals
could come under attack.

34:46.800 --> 34:51.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, in general, it's really
important to remember that
this just erodes the trust that

34:51.166 --> 34:55.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
allows humanitarians to do
work everywhere and get access
to the people who really need

34:55.633 --> 35:00.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
them the most, because
that often involves
really emphasizing the
fact that you are neutral

35:00.633 --> 35:04.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and not on the side of a
conflict, and so it's OK for
you to be serving people.

35:04.700 --> 35:09.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Eric Schmitt,
in your piece you remind us
that there was a more notorious

35:09.300 --> 35:14.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
incident where the CIA
was operating in Pakistan,
and it literally did
blur these very lines

35:15.166 --> 35:16.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that we're talking about.

35:16.366 --> 35:17.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Can you tell us what
happened in that story?

35:17.300 --> 35:19.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ERIC SCHMITT: Sure, absolutely.

35:19.366 --> 35:23.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In an effort to try and
determine whether Osama
bin Laden was actually
hiding in a walled

35:25.800 --> 35:29.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
compound in Abbottabad, in this
town in Pakistan, they devised
a system where they would go

35:31.900 --> 35:35.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
door-to-door in that city and
do inoculations, and hoping
that somebody would come to the

35:37.566 --> 35:40.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
door, they would be able to
come inside, take inoculations
from presumably family members,

35:40.533 --> 35:45.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and then get some type
of DNA readout on this.

35:45.266 --> 35:50.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, this all came to
light, of course, after
the death of bin Laden, and
it very much jeopardized

35:52.500 --> 35:57.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not only the doctors that were
involved, but it basically
turned much of that community

35:57.433 --> 35:59.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in Pakistan against
polio vaccinations.

35:59.800 --> 36:04.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, it became -- actually,
it was very counterproductive
for public health
reasons in that country.

36:04.733 --> 36:06.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And the CIA has said
it won't do that again.

36:06.866 --> 36:10.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Daryl
Grisgraber, what do you
-- what is your sense
of what revelations

36:10.766 --> 36:13.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
like this could do for the
effort in Yemen right now?

36:13.166 --> 36:16.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DARYL GRISGRABER: Well, there
are very few aid groups,
relatively speaking, operating

36:16.966 --> 36:19.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in Yemen as it is because
of the security situation.

36:19.933 --> 36:24.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are many U.N. agencies
and INGOs, international
non-governmental
organizations, that had to

36:25.666 --> 36:27.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
withdraw their staff.

36:27.700 --> 36:31.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so compared to the need
in Yemen, there are really
very few groups addressing it.

36:31.200 --> 36:36.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And if this breaks trust or
puts humanitarian under fire in
some way, it will be completely

36:36.200 --> 36:39.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
comprehensible that
organizations pull their
staffs out of there.

36:39.466 --> 36:43.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But that means even less
help for -- what are we
talking at, at this point?

36:43.166 --> 36:46.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Potentially, 17 million
people might begin starving
to death in a few weeks.

36:46.133 --> 36:50.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: All right,
Daryl Grisgraber, Eric Schmitt,
thank you both very much.

36:50.100 --> 36:54.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DARYL GRISGRABER: Thank you.

36:54.233 --> 36:58.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ERIC SCHMITT: Thank you.

36:58.333 --> 37:03.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: As the 2007 Tony
Awards approach this Sunday,
we look at one of this season's

37:07.233 --> 37:10.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
biggest Broadway hits and
the impact it's having.

37:10.733 --> 37:13.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown is back with
the story from New York.

37:13.866 --> 37:18.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: "Dear
Evan Hansen" is a high
school musical, but one
in which the loneliness

37:24.433 --> 37:29.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and pain of teen life is front
and center, and the sense
of isolation intensified in

37:30.300 --> 37:33.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
today's social media world.

37:33.000 --> 37:37.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At the famed Sardi's Restaurant
recently, star Ben Platt
said audiences are clearly

37:37.566 --> 37:39.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
finding a connection.

37:39.600 --> 37:43.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BEN PLATT, Actor: People that
come to the show feel, right
now, especially with sort

37:43.000 --> 37:46.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of hyperconnectivity online
and with people feeling sort
of instantaneously judged all

37:46.466 --> 37:51.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
the time, I think people
kind of recede into
these sort of bubbles.

37:51.166 --> 37:56.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The chance to sort of connect
and realize that nobody's
experience of loneliness is

37:58.966 --> 38:02.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
unique and that everybody at
some time or another feels
sort of on the outside looking

38:02.533 --> 38:07.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in, or feels that they can't
really fully be present, or
that they aren't sort of one

38:07.333 --> 38:12.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the whole, but rather
on their own, is a really
powerful thing right now.

38:14.266 --> 38:17.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The
23-year-old Platt grew up
around movies and theater.

38:20.533 --> 38:25.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
His father, Marc, is a
major producer of hits,
including "Wicked."

38:25.000 --> 38:30.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Before this production, Ben
was known for roles in the
"Pitch Perfect" films and in

38:34.633 --> 38:38.866 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
the musical "The
Book of Mormon."

38:38.866 --> 38:43.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
He plays Evan Hansen as
a young man so insecure,
he can barely speak.

38:43.433 --> 38:48.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's an acclaimed performance
of teenage awkwardness
and vibrant singing.

38:50.333 --> 38:53.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BEN PLATT: This role is
certainly the biggest challenge
I have had so far in my life.

38:55.766 --> 38:58.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's a huge blessing in that
way, too, because I feel like
I'm using all of the proverbial

38:58.833 --> 39:01.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
tools that I have in my belt,
which is all you want as an
actor, is to feel like you're

39:01.533 --> 39:04.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
really being able to show
everything you have got.

39:04.966 --> 39:08.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, vocally and physically
and emotionally and all of
that, it requires a lot.

39:08.233 --> 39:13.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: When a classmate
commits suicide, Evan Hansen
is mistakenly seen as his one

39:13.700 --> 39:15.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
friend.

39:15.733 --> 39:19.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Evan is suddenly a subject
of interest to his classmates
and the other boy's family.

39:21.433 --> 39:24.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He gains a girlfriend and even
a kind of instant celebrity when
a speech he gives about suicide

39:25.200 --> 39:26.966 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
goes viral.

39:26.966 --> 39:30.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it's all a misunderstanding,
destined to come crashing
down around him.

39:31.766 --> 39:33.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Steven Levenson wrote the story.

39:33.833 --> 39:35.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STEVEN LEVENSON, Author, "Dear
Evan Hansen": It's very much
this singular story of this

39:35.866 --> 39:40.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
person in the world that we
know very well, but struggling
with these things that hopefully

39:41.700 --> 39:43.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
